<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: HOLLYWOOD; WATER ERUPTS FROM 6 BROKEN PIPES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Water shot up from streets and sidewalks Tuesday after a series of mains 
ruptured under heavy pressure, but there was no major damage. 
</P>
<P>
 "It sure was strange to see," said Hollywood resident Joe Shea, who took a 
tour of the streets. "There were little fountains blowing right out of the 
sidewalk and out of the pavement, streams of water running down the middle of 
the street." 
</P>
<P>
 The six breaks were reported around Hollywood Boulevard and under the 
Hollywood Freeway on Monday night. Workers replaced ruptured portions of the 
pipes overnight and by 6:30 a.m. had restored service to the 40 customers who 
were cut off, authorities said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
