Keeler added four for visiting El Modena (7-3, 1-0), which beat Santa Ana 
Valley for the first time in four years. Santa Ana Valley is 0-1 in league. 
</P>
<P>
 Villa Park 15, Century 9 -- Freshman Kyle Baumgarner scored six goals for 
Villa Park (13-5, 1-0), in the league opener for both teams. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Freeway League: 
</P>
<P>
 Troy 11, Sunny Hills 10 OT -- Troy defeated Sunny Hills for the first time in 
27 years, giving the Lancers their second league loss in 24 years in the 
Freeway League. 
</P>
<P>
 Scott Backer, who had four assists, led Troy (12-3, 1-0) with six goals, 
including both overtime goals. Josh Batchelor had 15 saves. Sunny Hills is 
3-13, 0-1. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Orange League: 
</P>
<P>
 Brea-Olinda 24, Western 2 -- Sixth-ranked Brea-Olinda seemed to score at will 
against Western. Tad Murphy led the Wildcats with five goals and Jeff Ritter 
added four for host Brea-Olinda, which improved to 13-1, 2-0. Western dropped 
to 5-7, 0-1. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Sea View League: 
</P>
<P>
 Corona del Mar 13, El Toro 4 -- Adam McFarland and James Palda scored three 
goals each for third-ranked Corona del Mar (7-2, 1-0). Allen Basso scored three 
goals for visiting El Toro (11-3, 0-1), ranked sixth. 
</P>
<P>
 Newport Harbor 12, Irvine 7 -- Mike Peetz scored seven goals for ninth-ranked 
Newport Harbor (5-6, 1-0). Host Irvine is 6-8, 0-1. 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Margarita 6, Woodbridge 1 -- Steve Ferguson recorded 11 goalie saves for 
Santa Margarita (7-6, 1-0) leading them to their victory in the Sea View League 
opener. 
</P>
