<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOCAL NOTES: BROWN WON'T COACH SOFTBALL AT SADDLEBACK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Kim Brown, hired in August to coach Saddleback College's softball team, will 
not coach the team after all, the school said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 In a series of meetings between Brown and Athletic Director Bill Otta, it was 
decided that Brown would continue to teach an advanced softball class this 
semester, but not coach the intercollegiate team. 
</P>
<P>
 The coaching position remains open. For information, call 582-4850 or 
582-4547. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Bill Cunerty, Saddleback golf coach, has been elected to serve on the Southern 
California Golf Assn. board of directors. Cunerty's teams have won 12 
conference championships, four regional titles and four state titles in 13 
seasons. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Jay Larson of Huntington Beach and Chris Drummy of San Juan Capistrano posted 
the second and third highest heat totals in the trials of the Body Glove San 
Francisco Cup of the Bud Surf tour at Ocean Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 Larson and Drummy advance to Round 1 of the main event, along with Benji 
Severson of San Clemente. Competition continues today. 
</P>
