<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: LA PUENTE; $1,000 DONATED TOWARD GRAFFITI ERADICATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Young Hearts With Hope, a nonprofit graffiti prevention organization in La 
Puente, recently received a $1,000 donation from Kleen Kraft Services and the 
Alta-Dena Dairy. 
</P>
<P>
 Valerie Brannon, founder of the anti-graffiti group, will use the money to 
involve youths and their parents in painting vine murals over graffiti-defaced 
walls.Previously, Brannon painted vine murals on a wall at the Alta-Dena Dairy 
headquarters and production offices in the City of Industry. 
</P>
<P>
 The donation was made possible through a program in which Kleen Kraft, a 
uniform supply company based in the City of Commerce, donates 50 cents each 
time a company rents one of its "Say No to Drugs" entrance mats. More than 
$10,000 has been raised and donated to anti-drug and graffiti prevention groups 
in Southern California. 
</P>
</TEXT>
