<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY: CABRILLO VILLAGE; STOREFRONT STATION TO BOOST POLICE 
PRESENCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TRACY WILSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Hoping to improve community relations and ease gang-related fears, the Ventura 
Police Department plans to open a police storefront this weekend in Saticoy's 
Cabrillo Village, a community just east of Ventura. 
</P>
<P>
 The goal of the project is to address concerns of the residents living in the 
crime-plagued area and to establish neighborhood patrol programs. 
</P>
<P>
 A 37-year-old father of four was shot to death Saturday night after leaving a 
community meeting in Cabrillo Village. Police believe the man was the innocent 
victim of a gang-related incident. In 1991, two men were killed in the same 
neighborhood after leaving a party. 
</P>
<P>
 The storefront station will open Saturday and operate until Oct. 21. It will 
be open daily from noon to 6 p.m., and will be staffed by Ventura police 
officers and volunteers from the Cabrillo Village community. 
</P>
<P>
 Additionally, officers will patrol the area throughout the day and into the 
late evening and early morning hours. TRACY WILSON 
</P>
</TEXT>
