<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: THOUSAND OAKS; CAL LUTHERAN TO MARK FM STATION'S 
DEBUT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARY F. POLS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cal Lutheran University will celebrate the debut of its new public radio 
station, KCLU-FM, with a Sign-On Celebration from 4:30 to 6:30 p.m. Oct. 20. 
</P>
<P>
 KCLU-FM will be the first National Public Radio affiliate based in Ventura 
County.  
</P>
<P>
 About 500,000 listeners will be able to tune into the station, which will air 
national programs such as "Morning Edition," "Fresh Air" and "All Things 
Considered." 
</P>
<P>
 The celebration includes live jazz, refreshments and a chance for guests to 
record messages for use on KCLU-FM. Radio personality Norman Corwin is 
scheduled to give a brief presentation. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information about the party, contact Cal Lutheran's University 
Relations Office at 493-3151. MARY F. POLS 
</P>
</TEXT>
