<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: CARSON; WORKER DONATIONS WILL HELP SICK SEA MAMMALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SUSAN WOODWARD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 McDonnell Douglas employees have donated $5,000 to the Marine Mammal Care 
Center for sick and injured seals and sea lions. 
</P>
<P>
 The donation by the aerospace workers is the largest ever received by the 
nonprofit organization at Ft. MacArthur, director Don Zumwalt said. 
</P>
<P>
 The money will help enlarge the center, which has been operating for two 
years, Zumwalt said. "We're building a new 15,000-gallon tank and expanding our 
medical capabilities." 
</P>
<P>
 The marine center rescues and rehabilitates sea mammals from Los Angeles and 
Ventura county beaches before returning them to the sea. 
</P>
<P>
 The money was donated by employees of McDonnell Douglas West in Long Beach and 
Huntington Beach. SUSAN WOODWARD 
</P>
</TEXT>
