<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: SANTA MONICA; ALLRED 
LOSES SUIT AGAINST L.A. IN HER FATHER'S DEATH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Feminist attorney Gloria Allred lost a personal battle Wednesday when a Santa 
Monica jury ruled against her lawsuit alleging that incompetence by Los Angeles 
paramedics led to the death of her father, Morris Bloom. 
</P>
<P>
 The jury voted 10 to 2 in favor of the paramedics after 2 1/2 hours of 
deliberation after a three-week trial. 
</P>
<P>
 "I don't think it (the suit) was frivolous," said Deputy City Atty. Bob 
Pulone. "I firmly believe if Ms. Allred had known then what she does now" she 
would not have filed the suit. 
</P>
<P>
 Allred had alleged that paramedics were negligent when transporting her 
father, 89, from his Pacific Palisades home on Nov. 17, 1991. The suit said 
paramedics left Bloom on a gurney in front of the home, failing to notice 
eating and breathing tubes in his stomach and throat. 
</P>
<P>
 He died 18 days later in Santa Monica Hospital, which was also named in the 
suit. Allred had sought unspecified damages from the defendants. 
</P>
<P>
 Allred's attorney, Richard L. Knickerbocker, said he is considering an appeal. 
</P>
