</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A cashier in the Long Beach Planning and Building Department was arrested 
Wednesday and charged with stealing more than $150,000 in city funds. 
</P>
<P>
 Mary Alicia Valdez, 37, a resident of Bellflower, was being held in lieu of 
$205,000 bail.Long Beach police investigators said that Valdez, who has worked 
for the city for seven years, handled cash payments for building permits and 
other fees as part of her job. A co-worker discovered the theft in August and 
reported it to the police. 
</P>
<P>
 Charges of embezzlement and grand theft were filed against Valdez in Los 
Angeles Municipal Court by the district attorney's major fraud detail. 
</P>
<P>
 A city spokeswoman said that the city's insurance is expect to cover all but 
about $10,000 of the losses. 
