<TEXT>
<P>
 Chicago moved to fight gangs Wednesday by hanging up the phones they use for 
drug deals. The City Council approved without discussion a measure to ban 
outdoor pay phones on vacant buildings and lots, outside liquor stores and bars 
and on residential streets. 
</P>
<P>
 The ordinance will result in the immediate removal of about 500 phones, 
Revenue Director Judith Rice said. 
</P>
