<HEADLINE>
<P>
CRISIS IN THE CARIBBEAN; MARINE KILLED; SUICIDE SUSPECTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Marine apparently shot and killed himself aboard a ship that had been off 
Haiti, U.S. officials said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 They said Lance Cpl. Maurice Williams, 21, of Detroit was found dead in a 
sleeping area on the U.S. landing ship Nashville while it was in port in Puerto 
Rico. 
</P>
<P>
 The Nashville is one of a group of ships that landed about 1,800 Marines at 
Cap Haitien on Haiti's north coast when the U.S. military operation began Sept. 
19, and took them off this week. 
</P>
