<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY ALMANAC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 So you think your electric bill is high? 
</P>
<P>
 The Irvine Unified School District paid $2.4 million for electricity during 
the 1993-94 school year to operate 30 schools, as well as district offices and 
other facilities. 
</P>
<P>
 Total utility costs added up to $3.2 million, including a $391,049 phone bill, 
$287,782 for water and $100,440 for natural gas. 
</P>
<P>
 Overall, utility bills in the district rose by 4% compared to the 1992-93 
school year. How utility costs compared for 1993-94: Today 
</P>
<P>
 The Newport Harbor Area Chamber of Commerce will have its 10th Annual Business 
and Health Exposition at Fashion Island in Newport Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 Organizers said the event will be an opportunity for local businesses to show 
off their products and services in a relaxed environment that will include live 
entertainment, drinks and food. 
</P>
<P>
 The fair will run from 3 to 8 p.m. Admission is free. For more information, 
contact the chamber at (714) 729-4400. 
</P>
<P>
