<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: FINANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by James S. Granelli, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Doubling in Size: Frank Robitaille said he believes in controlled growth -- 
the kind that can double the size of a company in five years. 
</P>
<P>
 His insurance agency, Armstrong Robitaille Insurance Services in Tustin, has 
acquired its ninth Orange County firm since 1989 and is moving into the ranks 
of a regional organization. 
</P>
<P>
 The company acquired Perricone Insurance Agency in Newport Beach last month, 
picking up seven employees and a solid business writing various policies for 
companies in the food industry. 
</P>
<P>
 With up to 80 employees and $50 million in premiums expected this year, he 
said, Armstrong Robitaille has doubled its size in five years and plans to 
double its size again by 1999. 
</P>
<P>
 "I like controlled growth," said Robitaille, the agency's president. "All the 
acquisitions have been small operations that were easy to assimilate." 
</P>
<P>
 Future growth, though, is likely to be in other states. The agency recently 
opened an office in Ann Arbor, Mich., to serve the metal finishing and 
electroplating industry in the Midwest and East. 
</P>
</TEXT>
