<HEADLINE>
<P>
CITY HALL JOURNAL: MONTEBELLO; REPAIR-YARD, CULTURAL PROJECTS APPROVED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN D. WAGNER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The City Council has approved most of a $10-million plan to expand and 
renovate the city's vehicle-repair yard. 
</P>
<P>
 The yard, at 311 S. Greenwood Ave., will be extended across the street to 
Taylor and Colegrove avenues and expanded from 5.2 to 7.4 acres.A new 
administrative building, bus-washing facility, two-story parking structure and 
fueling area will be built. 
</P>
<P>
 Construction for the expansion is scheduled to start by January and end by 
late 1996. 
</P>
<P>
 The current yard was built in 1968 and is too small to service the fleet of 55 
city buses and some 200 city vehicles, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 The final phase of the project will be submitted to the council next year and 
will include plans to clean up some soil contaminated by leaking fuel lines. 
</P>
<P>
 Officials have also approved a $50,000 three-dimensional cultural art display 
on the past, present and future of Montebello. JOHN D. WAGNER 
</P>
</TEXT>
