<HEADLINE>
<P>
CITY HALL JOURNAL: DOWNEY; COUNCIL APPOINTS NEW CITY ATTORNEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The City Council has appointed its second city attorney since May. 
</P>
<P>
 Cheryl J. Kane has been hired to replace Timothy B. McOsker, who resigned 
Sept. 27 after about four months in order to accept a position as a deputy city 
attorney in Long Beach. McOsker also served as Downey's assistant city attorney 
from 1989 to 1993. 
</P>
<P>
 Kane, 48, is a partner with the Los Angeles law firm of Burke, Williams & 
Sorensen. She also serves as Moorpark's chief counsel. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
