<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: LONG BEACH; CIVIC LIGHT OPERA WILL RECEIVE $100,000 GRANT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The struggling Long Beach Civic Light Opera will receive $100,000 from the 
John S. and James L. Knight Foundation over three years, theater officials 
announced. 
</P>
<P>
 The Knight Foundation grant will help theater officials match a $490,000 
funding package offered by the city last month. The city funding will be 
available, provided the Civic Light Opera can raise a matching amount. 
</P>
<P>
 The theater has struggled with low ticket sales and mounting costs. This 
year's opening production, "Can-Can," was postponed from this month to January 
after two top officials departed this summer. 
</P>
</TEXT>
